commit.message:
Version 0.5

Version number in `setup.py` was changed.

Update CHANGELOG.rst

The changes in version 0.5.

Update README.rst

Added info mostly about ``unicode_argv``.

Support streams with no fileno attribute

In Python 2, StringIO doesn't have the `fileno` attribute at all, rather
than raising `io.UnsupportedOperation` as in Python 3. Fixes
https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/9639.

Set Unicode sys.argv

Setting Unicode `sys.argv` on Python 2 is now partially supported.

Use compile with dont_inherit=True

The runner compiles the code with `dont_inherit=True` on both Python 2
and 3, so `__future__` imports like `print_function` do not leak to the
code being run. Fixes #14.

For this, `tokenize.open` had to be backtported to detect the right
source encoding. Extra measures were taken since `compile` complains
about Unicode string containing encoding cookie in Python 2.

The runner prints traceback to `sys.stderr` and  in Python 2 tries to
handle encoding issues.

Merge pull request #27 from takluyver/patch-2

Update information on IPython compatibility
Grammar fix

Update information on IPython compatibility

Same as PR #26, but against development branch.

Fix typo in error message

A typo in an error message was fixed.

Disable readline hook on error

To avoid periodical exceptions from readline hook, the custom hook is
disabled after first internal error.

Enhance console detection

Detection whether a standard stream is a console and should be fixed was
enhanced. Also raising Windows errors was enhanced.

Remove superfluous cast

The argument type of `PyFile_AsFile` is already declared above.

Version 0.4-post

The version number in `setup.py` was changed.

Version 0.4

Version number in setup.py was changed. Also, the classifiers were
updated.

Get libc in a more robust way

Msvcrt / libc is now obtained in a more robust way.

Fix no-op on other platforms

I forgot to remove the unconditional import of `windll` in `streams`
module.

Add changelog

A changelog file was added. It reflects the release notes on GitHub.

Support no-op on other platforms

It is now possible to import ``win_unicode_console`` and its modules
also on platforms other than Windows. ``win_unicode_console.enable`` is
no-op there. Fixes #8.

Update README.rst

The readme file has been mostly rewritten.

Minor streams tweaks

Encoding of `StrStreamWrapper` is no longer fixed, a composition with a
transcoding wrapper should be used. Also, fileobject attribute
`writable` is now set.

Enhance the runner

The runner may now perform different actions before running a script –
enabling `win_unicode_console`, disabling it, no action, and importing
given module.

Detect KeyboardInerrupt in raw_input

The input functions in `raw_input` module now correctly raise
`KeyboardInterrupt`.

Minor tweaks

`check_PY2` is called before importing `__builtin__`, which is error
under Python 3. `raw_input_readline` and `readline_hook.stdio_readline`
have defaults for convenience.

Fix eval in raw_input

`eval` in `raw_input.input` is now called with correct globals and
locals retrieved from a caller.

Rename `assure_PY2` to `check_PY2`

`info.assure_PY2` was renamed to `info.check_PY2` for consistency.

Reset stdin encoding on Python 2

On Python 2, stdin fileobject encoding is now reset during each
readline, because when `win_unicode_console` is enabled in
sitecustomize, Py_Initialize changes the encoding afterwards.

`raw_input` may return both unicode or bytes

A parameter was added so `raw_input` function may return both unicode or
bytes objects. By default it returns unicode.

Update `readline_hook`

`RuntimeError` in `check_encodings` was changed to `RuntimeWarning`. The
condition when `pyreadline` is present but not active is detected, and
our readline hook is installed in that case.

raw_input update

`raw_input` was updated so it calls `PyOS_Readline` on interactive
stdio. Some tweaks of `readline_hook`.
